text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LanguageOfTheNacirema]]%0a%0a!Philosophy Lessons from PEDESTRIAN%0a%0a:Author: CharlieP%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aAnalysis of PEDESTRIAN in Nacirema Culture%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aYou should watch out for PEDESTRIANS when you're driving. You should know that crosswalks are for PEDESTRIANS. PEDESTRIAN-only roads are only for people walking, not for cars. Older cities had more PEDESTRIANS, but now more people drive. Frank was not one for such a PEDESTRIAN TV show, he would much rather watch an action movie. "This place is so PEDESTRIAN!" she exclaimed, after sitting in boredom for several hours. This model is less PEDESTRIAN than that one, but it costs more. %0a%0a%0aFrom the meaning of the word "pedestrian," you can see how the Nacirema people are incredibly focused on removing perambulatory means of movement, instead opting for mechanized methods, like cars or trains. "Pedestrian" has different meanings but is often used to describe someone who is walking alongside a road or on a sidewalk. "Pedestrian" additionally means that something is boring or dull. Typically, the people of the Nacirema don't like to be bored, so it is a common goal among the people to avoid "pedestrian" activities or places, instead opting for more interesting ventures. The use of the same word for these meanings shows that in Nacirema society and culture, walking in any form is seen as boring or beneath yourself, meaning that the Nacirema people would like to avoid walking at any cost. Even for Members of the Nacirema in dense urban areas, walking in any form is seen as undesirable, and many societal pushes are made to reduce infrastructure for people who walk. %0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: D:)%0a(:Category: LanguageOfTheNacirema:)
